</paragraph>
<paragraph id="430347556852FFF2A5ECD731FD96D024" blockId="3.[148,589,545,593]" box="[148,536,545,566]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A5ECD731FF6ED024" box="[148,224,545,566]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichini</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="272D3AA46852FFF2A596D731FED0D024" author="Kirby" box="[238,350,545,566]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" pagination="145 - 158" refId="ref3245" refString="Kirby, W. 1827. A description of some new genera and species of petalocerous Coleoptera. Zoological Journal 3 (10): 145 - 158." type="journal article" year="1827">Kirby 1827</bibRefCitation>
[original spelling].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0BA614DE6852FFF2A5ECD72CFE8AD120" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="430347556852FFF2A5ECD72CFDC3D043" blockId="3.[148,589,545,593]" box="[148,589,572,593]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A5ECD72CFEE2D043" authority=": Kirby 1837" authorityName=": Kirby" authorityYear="1837" box="[148,364,572,593]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Trichinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A5ECD72CFF61D043" box="[148,239,572,593]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichinus</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="272D3AA46852FFF2A585D72CFEE2D043" author="Kirby" box="[253,364,572,593]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" refId="ref3274" refString="Kirby, W. 1837. The insects. In: Fauna Boreali-Americana, part 4 (J. Richardson, W. Swainson, and W. Kirby, editors). Josiah Fletcher, Norwich. 325 pp." type="book" year="1837">Kirby 1837</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
[justified emendation].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="430347556852FFF2A5D4D773FE8AD120" blockId="3.[148,977,611,1058]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A5D4D773FE1ED06A" bold="true" box="[172,400,611,632]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Nomenclatural Status.</emphasis>
Available but invalid name, junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A625D773FE83D081" authority="Casey, 1915" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Trichiotinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A625D773FC5FD06A" box="[861,977,611,632]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichiotinus</emphasis>
Casey, 1915
</taxonomicName>
. Although 
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A40DD76EFE67D081" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1915" box="[373,489,638,659]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Trichiotinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A40DD76EFE67D081" box="[373,489,638,659]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichiotinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly in prevailing usage, Article 23.9.1 cannot be used for a reversal of precedence with 
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A754D789FD09D0BC" authorityName=": Kirby" authorityYear="1837" box="[556,647,665,686]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Trichinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A754D789FD09D0BC" box="[556,647,665,686]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because the latter name was used once in the past century as a valid name (by 
<bibRefCitation id="272D3AA46852FFF2A722D7A3FD41D0DA" author="Hatch &amp; The beetles of the Pacific northwest. Part &amp; Rhipiceroidea &amp; Sternoxi &amp; Phytophaga &amp; Rhynchophora &amp; Lamellicornia &amp; University of Washington Publications in Biology" box="[602,719,691,712]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" pagination="1 - 662" refId="ref3063" refString="Hatch, M. H. 1972. The beetles of the Pacific northwest. Part V: Rhipiceroidea, Sternoxi, Phytophaga, Rhynchophora, and Lamellicornia. University of Washington Publications in Biology 16: 1 - 662. [Dated 1971]." type="journal article" year="1972">Hatch 1972</bibRefCitation>
). Instead, I have made an application to the Commission of Zoological Nomenclature to conserve 
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A647D7DEFC3DD0F1" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1915" box="[831,947,718,739]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Trichiotinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A647D7DEFC3DD0F1" box="[831,947,718,739]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichiotinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by reversal of precedence with 
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A4E7D7F8FE74D0EF" authorityName=": Kirby" authorityYear="1837" box="[415,506,744,765]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Trichinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A4E7D7F8FE74D0EF" box="[415,506,744,765]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. While a decision is pending on this case, Article 82.1 of the Code instructs that the name in prevailing usage (
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A785D613FCFFD10A" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1915" box="[765,881,771,792]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Trichiotinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A785D613FCFFD10A" box="[765,881,771,792]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichiotinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) must be maintained.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0BA614DE6852FFF2A5D4D628FF7CD1FE" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" type="description">
<paragraph id="430347556852FFF2A5D4D628FF7CD1FE" blockId="3.[148,977,611,1058]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">
<bibRefCitation id="272D3AA46852FFF2A5D4D628FEDDD15F" author="Hoffmann" box="[172,339,824,845]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" pagination="133 - 209" refId="ref3150" refString="Hoffmann, C. H. 1935. The biology and taxonomy of the genus Trichiotinus (Scarabaeidae- Coleoptera). Entomologica Americana 15: 133 - 209." type="journal article" year="1935">Hoffmann (1935)</bibRefCitation>
discussed the usage of 
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A74ED628FD24D15F" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1915" box="[566,682,824,845]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Trichiotinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A74ED628FD24D15F" box="[566,682,824,845]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichiotinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A7A1D628FCBAD15F" authorityName=": Kirby" authorityYear="1837" box="[729,820,824,845]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Trichinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A7A1D628FCBAD15F" box="[729,820,824,845]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He rejected the usage of 
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A594D643FEB6D17A" box="[236,312,851,872]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichini</emphasis>
because Kirby ‘‘applied a plural ending to this... name.’’ However, Article 18.8.1 clearly states that such names should be considered available and directs taxonomists to emend the name to have the correct stem (in this case 
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A64AD698FF49D1A5" authority="Kirby, 1827" authorityName="Kirby. However" authorityYear="1827" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Trichinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A64AD698FC03D18F" box="[818,909,904,925]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="272D3AA46852FFF2A6EBD698FF49D1A5" author="Kirby" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" pagination="145 - 158" refId="ref3245" refString="Kirby, W. 1827. A description of some new genera and species of petalocerous Coleoptera. Zoological Journal 3 (10): 145 - 158." type="journal article" year="1827">Kirby, 1827</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="272D3AA46852FFF2A5A0D6B2FE0ED1A5" author="Hoffmann" box="[216,384,930,951]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" pagination="133 - 209" refId="ref3150" refString="Hoffmann, C. H. 1935. The biology and taxonomy of the genus Trichiotinus (Scarabaeidae- Coleoptera). Entomologica Americana 15: 133 - 209." type="journal article" year="1935">Hoffmann (1935)</bibRefCitation>
also considered 
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A759D6B2FC8ED1A5" authority="Meigen, 1830" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1830" box="[545,768,930,951]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Trichina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A759D6B2FDFDD1A5" box="[545,627,930,951]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichina</emphasis>
Meigen, 1830
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A675D6B2FCD7D1A5" box="[781,857,930,951]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A61AD6B2FC44D1A5" box="[866,970,930,951]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Empididae</taxonomicName>
) to be a homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A425D6ADFDD2D1C0" authority="Kirby. However" authorityName="Kirby. However" authorityYear="1827" box="[349,604,957,978]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Trichinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A425D6ADFE36D1C0" box="[349,440,957,978]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichinus</emphasis>
Kirby. However
</taxonomicName>
, these names are not homonyms under the Code.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0BA614DE6852FFF2A5D4D6E2FD8ED630" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="430347556852FFF2A5D4D6E2FD8ED630" blockId="3.[148,977,611,1058]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A5D4D6E2FECCD615" bold="true" box="[172,322,1010,1031]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">
<typeStatus id="9C07F9F76852FFF2A5D4D6E2FF6ED615" box="[172,224,1010,1031]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Type</typeStatus>
Species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A436D6E2FD1DD615" authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[334,659,1010,1031]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Trichius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piger">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A436D6E2FE6FD615" box="[334,481,1010,1031]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichius piger</emphasis>
Fabricius, 1775
</taxonomicName>
(now 
<taxonomicName id="84BC3CD66852FFF2A79FD6E2FC11D615" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[743,927,1010,1031]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Trichiotinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piger">
<emphasis id="71C89B476852FFF2A79FD6E2FC11D615" box="[743,927,1010,1031]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Trichiotinus piger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by subsequent designation (
<bibRefCitation id="272D3AA46852FFF2A4F9D11DFE7AD630" author="Kirby" box="[385,500,1037,1058]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" refId="ref3274" refString="Kirby, W. 1837. The insects. In: Fauna Boreali-Americana, part 4 (J. Richardson, W. Swainson, and W. Kirby, editors). Josiah Fletcher, Norwich. 325 pp." type="book" year="1837">Kirby 1837</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
